ated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Margarete","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretha","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margrethe Knudsdatter was born in Denmark as the daughter of Knud Lavard and Ingeborga Mstislavsdatter (Mstislavna) of Novgorod/Kiev, Queen of Denmark. She had at least 4 sons and 1 daughter with Stig Tokesen Hvide. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1118–1139":"1118–1139","1125–Female":"1125–Surnud","1127–Female":"1127–Surnud","1129–Female":"1129–Surnud","1131–1182":"1131–1182","–Female":"Surnud","1110–1151":"1110–1151","1145–1200":"1145–1200","–1214":"–1214","–Male":"Surnud","1096–1131":"1096–1131","1099–1137":"1099–1137","1099":"1099","1110":"1110","1131":"1131","1096":"1096","1151":"1151","1182":"1182","1129":"1129","1118":"1118","1139":"1139","1116":"1116","1127":"1127","1137":"1137","1214":"1214","1125":"1125","1200":"1200","1145":"1145","about 1145":"umbes 1145","Denmark":"Taani"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1118–1139":"1118–1139","1125–Female":"1125–Kuollut","1127–Female":"1127–Kuollut","1129–Female":"1129–Kuollut","1131–1182":"1131–1182","–Female":"Kuollut","1110–1151":"1110–1151","1145–1200":"1145–1200","–1214":"–1214","–Male":"Kuollut","1096–1131":"1096–1131","1099–1137":"1099–1137","1099":"1099","1110":"1110","1131":"1131","1096":"1096","1151":"1151","1182":"1182","1129":"1129","1118":"1118","1139":"1139","1116":"1116","1127":"1127","1137":"1137","1214":"1214","1125":"1125","1200":"1200","1145":"1145","